cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MS, cs.AI, cs.MM

This paper deals with the application of deep learning for image recognition and analysis of chest X-ray images. The focus is on lung segmentation and bone shadow exclusion techniques, which are important for identifying suspicious lesions and nodules in lung cancer patients. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms, particularly deep learning, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves medical imaging, which could place it in cs.MS (Medical Imaging). The use of deep learning for image recognition and analysis also suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of 2D CXRs, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia).
